  "response": "There are no verified photographs of Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj as he lived in the 17th century and the camera was not invented until the 19th century. However, there have been several artistic representations and paintings of Shivaji Maharaj created by various artists over the years. One of the well-known artists who created a portrait of Shivaji Maharaj is Mir Muhammad, during Shivaji's lifetime.\n\nThe painting by Mir Muhammad is an important historical artifact that has been used by historians to understand Shivaji Maharaj's appearance. However, it's essential to note that this painting, like others from that era, is an artistic interpretation and may not be an exact representation.\n\nTo view this specific painting, you can look through historical archives or visit museums that house collections of artifacts related to Shivaji Maharaj and his life. Such images are also often available online through historical and educational websites.",
